<BaseLayout
  title="Holistic Pharmacy & Wellness Consultation | Four Winds Roots Pharmacy, North York"
  description="Holistic pharmacy care at Four Winds Roots, Keele & Finch, North York. Herb-drug interaction reviews, wellness consultations, and whole-person pharmacy support. Call (416) 398-8200."
>
  <!--
    IA KEY BLOCKS (from information-architecture.md — Holistic Wellness):
    1. ServiceHero — "Whole-person care at your corner pharmacy" headline + consult CTA
    2. What holistic care means here — plain language: herb-drug interaction review, wellness
       guidance, listening to the whole picture. NOT medical advice, NOT disease treatment claims.
    3. Who it's for — EligibilityNote: people managing complex regimens, supplements users,
       anyone who wants more than a prescription hand-off
    4. How to start — StepList: book a consult, bring your med/supplement list, private conversation
    5. Compounding — if offered; TODO: confirm with owner whether compounding is available
    6. Clear non-overclaiming language — legal/compliance note: "guidance, not medical diagnosis"
    7. BookingCTA — phone or scheduler
    Primary keyword: "holistic pharmacy North York", "herb drug interaction review"
    BRAND NOTE: this page should feel warm and distinctive — not clinical, not new-age.
    LEGAL: Do not publish any specific health claims without review by the owner/OCP.
  -->

  <!--
    OCP COMPLIANCE NOTE (do not delete):
    This page requires OCP advertising review before go-live (Task #29).
    "Registered holistic pharmacy that deals with herbs and drug interactions" is
    the confirmed directory descriptor (Ontario Health atHome, March 2026) and is
    safe to use. Do NOT add disease treatment claims, clinical outcomes, or
    patient testimonials without OCP review and explicit consent.
    "Natural Health Practitioner" is not a regulated RHPA title — Pamela Clarke
    must be described factually, not as a regulated health professional.
  -->

  <div class="container section">
    <h1>Holistic Pharmacy &amp; Wellness at Keele &amp; Finch</h1>
    <p>
      Four Winds Roots is a <strong>registered holistic pharmacy that deals with herbs and
      drug interactions</strong> — looking at the whole person, not just the prescription.
      Bring us your full list: medications, herbs, vitamins, and supplements. We'll help
      you understand how everything works together.
    </p>
    <p>
      <PhoneLink class="btn btn-call" display="Call to Book a Consultation" />
    </p>

    <section aria-labelledby="holistic-what-it-means">
      <h2 id="holistic-what-it-means">What Holistic Pharmacy Care Means Here</h2>
      <p>
        At most pharmacies, the conversation ends when you pick up your prescription.
        At Four Winds Roots, it begins there. Our holistic approach means we consider
        your full health picture before, during, and after dispensing:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Reviewing how your prescriptions interact with herbs and natural supplements</li>
        <li>Flagging combinations that could reduce effectiveness or cause side effects</li>
        <li>Discussing wellness goals alongside your medication plan</li>
        <li>Giving you time — not just a hand-off</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <em>
          This complements your medical care — it does not replace your doctor or prescriber.
          <!-- TODO: OCP advertising review of this section before publishing (Task #29) -->
        </em>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="holistic-who-its-for">
      <h2 id="holistic-who-its-for">Who This Is For</h2>
      <p>
        Our holistic pharmacy care is especially valuable for anyone who:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Takes herbal remedies or natural supplements alongside prescriptions</li>
        <li>Wants to understand what they're taking and why</li>
        <li>Is managing multiple medications and seeking a fuller picture</li>
        <li>Prefers a whole-person conversation rather than a transactional pharmacy visit</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="holistic-herb-drug">
      <h2 id="holistic-herb-drug">Herb-Drug Interaction Review</h2>
      <p>
        Many common herbs and supplements can interact with prescription medications —
        affecting how a drug is absorbed, how quickly it leaves your body, or whether
        it reaches the right concentration to work. St. John's Wort, ginkgo, garlic
        supplements, and many others have well-documented interactions with common
        prescription drugs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Bring your full list — prescription and over-the-counter — and we'll walk through
        any potential interactions together. For a structured review, a
        <a href="/services/medication-reviews">free MedsCheck medication review</a>
        covers this in detail.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="holistic-wellness-practitioner">
      <h2 id="holistic-wellness-practitioner">Our Wellness Practitioner</h2>
      <!--
        COMPLIANCE NOTE: Pamela Clarke is described exactly as listed in the Ontario Health
        atHome directory — "Natural Health Practitioner". This is NOT a regulated title.
        Do not add credentials, clinical claims, or RN designation.
      -->
      <p>
        <strong>Pamela Clarke</strong>, our Natural Health Practitioner, brings a whole-person
        perspective to the wellness side of our practice. Pamela focuses on natural health,
        herb safety, and helping patients take an active role in their wellbeing — the philosophy
        behind her book, <em>Take Control Now: Your Health Is Your Responsibility</em>
        (FriesenPress, 2015).
      </p>
      <p>
        <!-- TODO: confirm with owner the specific wellness services Pamela offers at this location -->
        <!-- TODO: OCP advertising review of this section before publishing (Task #29) -->
        <em>Speak with our team about wellness consultations — call or visit us.</em>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="holistic-compounding">
      <h2 id="holistic-compounding">Compounding</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- TODO: confirm whether compounding is offered at this location and to what scope with owner.
             Note: compounding is NOT confirmed at Four Winds Roots from public directory data.
             Do not publish this section until confirmed. -->
        <em>Compounding services — details coming soon. Call us to ask about availability.</em>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="holistic-how-to-start">
      <h2 id="holistic-how-to-start">How to Start</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Call us or stop by — let us know you'd like a holistic wellness consultation.</li>
        <li>Bring your complete medication and supplement list (or a photo of your bottles).</li>
        <li>We'll sit down in private and work through everything together.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        <PhoneLink class="btn btn-call" display="Call (416) 398-8200" />
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
